## C3: review-consumption tracking

Option (a) — decider writes `popped_by_queue_id` onto the review file at pop time. Prevents one review file from popping N queue items.

The matcher treats a review as "already consumed" when its `popped_by_queue_id` is set to any value **other than the current item's queue_id** — a review that's already been claimed by qid 163 is no longer available to also claim qid 171. A review never popped has `popped_by_queue_id` absent.

